17:06.659 --> 17:09.761
Can you account for yourself
on march 23rd of this year?

17:09.762 --> 17:12.730
        [ Chuckling ] I don't
        even know what day of
        the week that was, Carl.

17:12.732 --> 17:16.567
  It was a Tuesday.
            okay, if you say so.

17:16.569 --> 17:18.669
            I mean, I could look
           at my weekly planner,

17:18.671 --> 17:21.138
      See what I had on my plate
         that particular day.

17:21.141 --> 17:24.308
It was the day
after Daniel Holden
got released from prison.

17:24.310 --> 17:27.645
     Now, I remember that day --
        the day he got out --

17:27.646 --> 17:31.449
   But the day after was just...
      another day to me, Carl.

17:31.451 --> 17:33.618
Sinclair cash and carry
     ring a bell?

17:33.620 --> 17:37.121
            I know the place.
          it don't ring no bell.

17:37.123 --> 17:40.291
You bought gas there, paid cash.
               didn't happen.

17:40.293 --> 17:41.526
    Got a witness.

17:43.463 --> 17:46.330
    Now, who the hell's gonna
 remember me coming into a place

17:46.332 --> 17:49.333
             On an exact day
         six or seven weeks ago?

17:49.335 --> 17:51.135
       Somebody
who will swear to it.

17:51.137 --> 17:52.603
                   Well,
            I’ll swear I didn't.

17:52.605 --> 17:56.674
                      ¶¶

18:03.483 --> 18:06.417
When was the last time
you talked to Chris Nelms?

18:08.588 --> 18:10.288
              Couldn't tell you.

18:10.290 --> 18:12.190
      Last time
you called him, then.

18:12.192 --> 18:13.691
                  [ Sighs ]

18:13.693 --> 18:16.227
       About the same time
  I was shooting them squirrels.

18:16.229 --> 18:17.728
              He didn't answer.

18:17.730 --> 18:20.598
 You leave a message?

18:20.600 --> 18:22.366
                I might have.

18:22.368 --> 18:24.435
       Remember
  what it was about?

18:24.437 --> 18:27.305
              Couldn't tell you
                  verbatim.

18:27.307 --> 18:30.641
What if I could tell <I>you
      verbatim?

18:35.348 --> 18:38.116
              [ Gulps ]
      I’d take your word for it.

18:41.588 --> 18:43.754
Something bothering you,
        Trey?

18:45.658 --> 18:47.658
       That son of a bitch
             told me

18:47.660 --> 18:50.661
       He was gonna get me
        some kettle corn.

18:50.663 --> 18:52.530
               I forgot, Carl.

18:52.532 --> 18:53.798
   Could you still
   make good on it?

18:53.800 --> 18:55.299
           We ate the whole bag.

18:55.301 --> 18:57.435
  Is there any more
    in the pantry?

18:57.437 --> 18:59.403
                 I'll check.
                  [ sighs ]

19:01.741 --> 19:05.610
      [ Door opens, closes ]

19:05.612 --> 19:06.811
                   [ Sighs ]

19:06.813 --> 19:11.182
    Be nice to stay in one place
            for a while.

19:11.184 --> 19:12.517
              Other than Paulie.

19:12.519 --> 19:14.152
 It'll be different.

19:14.154 --> 19:16.654
              Boston and Paulie?
                   really?

19:16.656 --> 19:19.357
Boston has the Celtics.

19:19.359 --> 19:20.858
                    Right.

19:20.860 --> 19:23.661
But then, the skating rinks
   are nicer here.

19:23.663 --> 19:25.496
                    Rink.

19:25.498 --> 19:30.501
    So, you're gonna carry on
   with the thrifty town plan?

19:30.503 --> 19:33.838
   That's the plan
       for now.

19:33.840 --> 19:35.573
           [ Chuckles ]

19:35.575 --> 19:38.442
    You know, I never would have
     thought in a million years

19:38.444 --> 19:40.411
           You'd be in this town
             if Daniel wasn't.

19:42.482 --> 19:45.349
         I never thought
      a lot of things, Jon.

19:45.351 --> 19:48.920
                      ¶¶

19:53.259 --> 19:55.927
                  [ Sighs ]
                   well...

19:55.929 --> 19:58.796
   I'm gonna go on with my life,
                too.

19:58.798 --> 20:00.765
            And that may lead me
             to something else.

20:04.370 --> 20:06.237
             I know.

20:06.239 --> 20:08.339
                Glad you know.

20:08.341 --> 20:11.943
                  [ Sighs ]

20:11.945 --> 20:15.713
               Well, I guess
           I’d better get going.

20:17.517 --> 20:20.685
            Thank you.

20:20.687 --> 20:22.420
    For all that you've done,
               Jon.

20:22.422 --> 20:24.989
      I didn't do anything worth
           thanking me for.

20:24.991 --> 20:26.457
         That's not true.

20:26.459 --> 20:27.959
             We both know
     he would've been better off

20:27.961 --> 20:30.328
             With somebody else.

20:30.330 --> 20:31.862
                   Somebody
               less distracted.

20:37.670 --> 20:41.606
                      ¶¶

20:48.982 --> 20:52.250
                      ¶¶

21:16.009 --> 21:19.277
                      ¶¶

21:27.720 --> 21:30.421
Daniel: sometimes I...

21:30.423 --> 21:35.760
Wanted to walk to the front gate
  and ask them to...

21:35.762 --> 21:38.529
   Let me back in.

21:39.966 --> 21:42.500
  Back into my box.

21:42.502 --> 21:45.670
      My cocoon.

21:45.672 --> 21:49.540
That's not right thinking,
       mother.

21:49.542 --> 21:52.743
           You're not the first
          to romance the cocoon.

21:55.682 --> 21:57.848
  [ Inhales deeply ]

21:57.850 --> 21:59.417
   But not today.
 [ exhales deeply ]

21:59.419 --> 22:01.585
        Today,
I want to go to the beach.

22:01.587 --> 22:03.587
    I want to feel
the sand between my toes

22:03.589 --> 22:05.589
     And look up
at that infinite sky.

22:05.591 --> 22:09.927
          As fate would have it,
                 so do I.

22:09.929 --> 22:13.798
And I want to tell you
about my friend Kerwin.

22:15.568 --> 22:18.536
        He was
  something special.

22:18.538 --> 22:20.538
                  I'd love
           to hear about Kerwin.

22:20.540 --> 22:23.874
 And I want to drive.

22:23.876 --> 22:25.876
   I want to drive
with the windows down,

22:25.878 --> 22:27.845
Even if it is raining.

22:27.847 --> 22:31.649
 At least 4 1/2 miles
over the speed limit.

22:31.651 --> 22:34.385
            I will brace myself,
                   then.

22:34.387 --> 22:36.821
     [ Chuckles ]

22:36.823 --> 22:39.924
         [ Door beeping ]

22:39.926 --> 22:43.728
                      ¶¶

22:48.701 --> 22:51.702
   Chris Nelms said
  y'all raped Hanna.

22:51.704 --> 22:53.371
                 He's lying.

22:53.373 --> 22:55.573
   Why would he lie
     about that?

22:57.543 --> 23:01.045
       Y'all didn't tell him
   it was George’s DNA, did you?

23:01.047 --> 23:03.581
              The single sample.

23:03.583 --> 23:06.450
         Chris still thinks
    it might be his, doesn't he?

23:06.452 --> 23:09.153
You know a lot about DNA
for an electrician, Trey.

23:09.155 --> 23:11.021
                Uh-huh.
       you made a deal with him.

23:11.023 --> 23:12.590
 You raped her, Trey.

23:12.592 --> 23:14.592
              It was consensual.

23:14.594 --> 23:17.094
At least now you're admitting to
having sex with her that night.

23:17.096 --> 23:18.929
    That's a step
in the right direction.

23:18.931 --> 23:21.632
          This is all messed up,
                  Carl.

23:21.634 --> 23:23.501
George was gonna spill
the beans, wasn't he?

23:23.503 --> 23:25.503
              [ Laughing ]
       you got it so wrong, man.

23:25.505 --> 23:26.837
            It ain't even funny.

23:26.839 --> 23:29.407
         So,
let me get this straight.

23:29.409 --> 23:32.576
The guy at Sinclair’s is lying
about you being in his store

23:32.578 --> 23:34.445
    Near the area
  of the flint river

23:34.447 --> 23:36.747
 Where George’s body
was eventually found.

23:36.749 --> 23:38.916
           He could have floated
              for miles, Carl.

23:38.918 --> 23:41.619
Putting you near there
   on the same day

23:41.621 --> 23:44.655
George arrived in Paulie
  by greyhound bus.

23:44.657 --> 23:48.159
And Chris Nelms is lying that
  y'all raped Hanna,

23:48.161 --> 23:51.061
 Which would give you
motive to keep George
from ratting you out.

23:51.063 --> 23:53.431
  And then finally,
Daniel Holden is lying

23:53.433 --> 23:56.100
About you having possession
of George’s wallet and phone,

23:56.102 --> 23:58.636
    Which we know
was in Paulie on the 23rd

23:58.638 --> 24:03.641
But somehow made their way back
to George’s trailer in live oak

24:03.643 --> 24:05.009
After George was dead.

24:05.011 --> 24:08.946
           Holden put 'em there.
                  not me.

24:08.948 --> 24:12.216
Oh, and your own voicemail
to Chris Nelms is lying, too.

24:15.054 --> 24:17.755
                 I never said
              anything specific

24:17.757 --> 24:21.158
             About anybody
        in that voicemail, Carl.

24:21.160 --> 24:24.228
   People can read
between the lines, Trey.

24:24.230 --> 24:26.230
                  [ Scoffs ]

24:26.232 --> 24:29.533
You think the whole world's
full of idiots, don't you?

24:29.535 --> 24:32.536
                 [ Chuckles ]

24:32.538 --> 24:34.772
                 The world is
               full of idiots.

24:36.943 --> 24:39.109
            And I’m one of them.

24:39.111 --> 24:40.578
   It's over, Trey.

24:40.580 --> 24:43.481
  I don't even need
a confession from you.

24:43.483 --> 24:45.149
     I'd suggest
you just shut your mouth

24:45.151 --> 24:47.218
  And call a lawyer
      right now.

24:49.021 --> 24:52.990
        This is so crazy, Carl.
       I -- listen -- all right.

24:54.894 --> 24:58.262
             I'm gonna tell you
           what really happened.

24:58.264 --> 25:01.098
             But you ain't gonna
                 believe it.

25:01.100 --> 25:02.867
                 I'm serious.

25:02.869 --> 25:04.668
   Give her a shot.

25:04.670 --> 25:08.839
           I didn't kill George.
              I swear to god.

25:08.841 --> 25:10.040
        Okay.

25:10.042 --> 25:12.543
              See? I knew
        you wouldn't believe me.

25:12.545 --> 25:15.212
  Who killed George,
     then, Trey?

25:15.214 --> 25:16.547
                   Nobody.

25:16.549 --> 25:18.883
  Nobody?
               I mean <I>he did.

25:18.885 --> 25:20.751
George killed himself?
                      yes!

25:20.753 --> 25:21.852
                        Bam!

25:23.523 --> 25:27.591
            See? I told you
        you wouldn't believe me.

25:29.262 --> 25:33.631
      [ Sighs ]

25:33.633 --> 25:36.800
I'd like to believe you, Trey.
   I really would.

25:36.802 --> 25:39.303
But there's just too many things
  that don't add up.

25:39.305 --> 25:41.672
                Well,
      I can explain them to you.

25:41.674 --> 25:44.842
     Okay, Trey.
    explain away.

25:46.679 --> 25:49.747
                      ¶¶

26:25.217 --> 26:27.918
      I'm sorry
   Hoppy’s is gone.

26:27.920 --> 26:29.920
                They razed it.

26:29.922 --> 26:32.623
It was kind of ratty,
   even back then.

26:32.625 --> 26:33.958
                   Heretic.

26:33.960 --> 26:35.693
    [ Chuckling ]
   I’m just saying.

26:35.695 --> 26:39.029
                  At least
            they kept the beach.

26:39.031 --> 26:41.198
       I think
it was grandfathered in.

26:41.200 --> 26:43.901
       This is the perfect spot,
                mother.

26:43.903 --> 26:46.370
  [ Inhales deeply ]
     it sure is.

26:46.372 --> 26:48.272
        [ Child laughing ]

26:55.881 --> 27:00.050
     I read some more on the
  new Canaan project last night.

27:00.052 --> 27:01.952
         Talked to Jon about it.

27:01.954 --> 27:03.787
       You did?

27:03.789 --> 27:06.790
            Yeah, thinking about
               the programs.

27:06.792 --> 27:08.325
              The possibilities,
                   I guess.

27:08.327 --> 27:10.828
      They have
a great success rate.

27:10.830 --> 27:14.331
              Maybe I can get...

27:14.333 --> 27:17.034
                 More normal.

27:17.036 --> 27:18.736
            Run for dog catcher.

27:29.815 --> 27:32.149
              Is this your ball?

27:32.151 --> 27:34.818
               M-may I throw it
                   to you?

27:36.689 --> 27:37.988
                     Oh.
    [ clapping ]

27:37.990 --> 27:39.823
That was one of the best catches
I’ve seen,

27:39.825 --> 27:42.092
    Well, in all my years.

27:42.094 --> 27:43.794
     I catch it all the time.

27:43.796 --> 27:46.797
           I stand before you
       astonished and astounded.

27:46.799 --> 27:49.166
      You can throw it again
           if you want.

27:49.168 --> 27:52.903
               I'd be honoured,
                  young sir.

27:55.675 --> 27:56.840
           Dare we hope for two?

27:59.445 --> 28:00.678
                  [ Gasps ]

28:00.680 --> 28:04.014
                 Fantastical!
                stupor-pendus!

28:04.016 --> 28:07.017
              Uh...

28:07.019 --> 28:08.819
     I kind of got to go now.

28:08.821 --> 28:11.355
               All good things.

28:11.357 --> 28:16.026
                      ¶¶

28:18.330 --> 28:20.831
      You're good with kids.

28:20.833 --> 28:22.399
    Was that good?

28:22.401 --> 28:25.302
      I certainly think so.

28:25.304 --> 28:28.238
               Beginner's luck.

28:30.176 --> 28:33.343
                I must now go
                to the source.

28:33.345 --> 28:35.879
  Of course. enjoy.

28:44.056 --> 28:45.422
Make sure you come back.

28:53.833 --> 28:58.769
                      ¶¶

30:20.853 --> 30:23.187
                   What are
               you doing here?

30:23.189 --> 30:25.956
 I came to visit you,
       Daniel.

30:25.958 --> 30:28.358
            That's not possible.

30:28.360 --> 30:31.361
     [ Chuckles ]
       I know.

30:31.363 --> 30:34.064
               You're not here,
                   are you?

30:34.066 --> 30:36.433
You're not here either,
       Daniel.

30:36.435 --> 30:39.136
              Well, where am I?

30:39.138 --> 30:42.573
 You're at the beach
   with your mama.

30:42.575 --> 30:45.442
            That's unimaginable.

30:45.444 --> 30:47.477
    But it's true.

30:47.479 --> 30:51.982
  And it's glorious.
    I know it is.

30:51.984 --> 30:56.453
                      ¶¶

31:05.397 --> 31:07.631
                Where are you,
                   Tawney?

31:09.168 --> 31:11.168
    I don't know.

31:11.170 --> 31:15.038
               You don't know?

31:15.040 --> 31:17.441
  I'm lost, Daniel.

31:20.145 --> 31:22.479
 And it's so lonely.
       [ sobs ]

31:22.481 --> 31:24.348
I'll come and find you.

31:24.350 --> 31:27.618
                  You can't.
              I need to find me.

31:27.620 --> 31:30.287
   What about god?

31:30.289 --> 31:31.922
                     God?

31:31.924 --> 31:33.590
    As your guide.

31:33.592 --> 31:37.594
  God doesn't exist.

31:37.596 --> 31:40.130
            Of course he exists.

31:40.132 --> 31:42.032
  Tell me the truth,
       Daniel.

31:42.034 --> 31:45.369
      This time,
  tell me the truth.

31:45.371 --> 31:48.906
             You know the truth,
                   Tawney.

31:48.908 --> 31:53.143
 Then w-where is he?
    where is god?

31:53.145 --> 31:55.412
             You know that, too.

31:55.414 --> 31:59.683
   I used to know.
  before I met you.

31:59.685 --> 32:01.652
             But you still know.

32:03.522 --> 32:06.223
In between the seconds?

32:06.225 --> 32:07.591
                     Yes.

32:07.593 --> 32:11.194
You told me too much,
       Daniel.

32:13.098 --> 32:14.965
     I was happy.

32:14.967 --> 32:17.467
                You remember.

32:17.469 --> 32:22.172
        God is in the flowers...

32:22.174 --> 32:24.675
              And in the rain...

32:24.677 --> 32:26.643
              And in your tears.

32:26.645 --> 32:29.346
 God is in my tears?

32:29.348 --> 32:32.716
            I've seen him there,
                  lurking.

32:32.718 --> 32:36.253
You're a false prophet.

32:36.255 --> 32:39.056
   I'm gonna tell you something,
              Tawney.

32:39.058 --> 32:41.224
 I won't believe you.

32:41.226 --> 32:43.994
             God is a rain frog.

32:45.597 --> 32:51.468
           As god is my witness.
             he's a rain frog.

32:51.470 --> 32:54.438
                   May frog
               strike me down.

32:54.440 --> 32:58.475
     [ Laughing ]
 you're mad, Daniel.

32:58.477 --> 33:01.311
             And so must be god.

33:07.186 --> 33:09.052
 I'm gonna miss you.

33:09.054 --> 33:11.989
              The hardest part.

33:11.991 --> 33:15.726
                      ¶¶

33:24.269 --> 33:27.704
  There's no glass.

33:27.706 --> 33:29.606
             Sometimes there is.

33:29.608 --> 33:34.244
Sometimes there isn't.

33:38.484 --> 33:42.019
               I could kiss you
                 right here.

33:42.021 --> 33:46.690
   I-I don't know,
       Daniel.

33:46.692 --> 33:50.227
               We're unguarded.

33:50.229 --> 33:52.229
    I'm afraid to.

33:52.231 --> 33:56.400
           This isn't even real,
                  Tawney.

33:56.402 --> 33:58.402
But won't it feel real?

33:58.404 --> 34:01.671
               God, I hope so.

34:01.673 --> 34:05.142
   You may kiss me,
       Daniel.

34:05.144 --> 34:09.079
                      ¶¶

34:29.268 --> 34:31.333
        [ Birds chirping ]

34:32.670 --> 34:36.606
                     Sir?
             you have a visitor.

34:44.716 --> 34:46.650
      [ Sighs ]

34:51.790 --> 34:54.558
 We just never know,
        do we?

34:57.329 --> 34:59.830
I'm told you still have your
cognitive abilities, senator.

34:59.832 --> 35:04.201
   That's something
 to be grateful for.

35:04.203 --> 35:05.535
       Or maybe
that's more the burden now.

35:05.537 --> 35:09.406
Anyway, I assume the sheriff
 has kept you abreast

35:09.408 --> 35:11.842
 On the investigation
of the murder of George Melton.

35:13.779 --> 35:15.812
                Or maybe not.

35:15.814 --> 35:18.815
Sheriff Daggett is preparing
to arrest Trey Willis

35:18.817 --> 35:20.517
For Mr. Melton’s murder.

35:20.519 --> 35:25.889
What has me curious is,
         why?

35:25.891 --> 35:29.659
Why would Trey Willis
murder George Melton?

35:31.697 --> 35:36.399
The obvious answer is
because they raped Hanna dean.

35:36.401 --> 35:38.535
 And Trey was afraid
George would implicate him.

35:38.537 --> 35:40.704
You're probably already
  ahead of me here,

35:40.706 --> 35:45.242
     But the flaw
   in that premise

35:45.244 --> 35:47.811
Is the statute of limitations
on the rape charge itself.

35:52.918 --> 35:56.786
    It's 15 years
    in Georgia...

35:56.788 --> 36:00.857
 Unless there is DNA
tying the suspect to the rape.

36:02.828 --> 36:04.761
      Would Trey
    not know that?

36:06.598 --> 36:08.298
    So, naturally,
  one has to wonder

36:08.300 --> 36:11.268
If there wasn't a greater crime
 George knew about --

36:11.270 --> 36:14.671
       A crime
with no statute of limitations.

36:14.673 --> 36:19.376
It's still a bit of a mystery,
but the one thing I’m sure of...

36:19.378 --> 36:21.811
Is you are dirty here,
       senator,

36:21.813 --> 36:24.915
And I’m gonna find out
      how dirty.

36:24.917 --> 36:26.349
               And I’m going
            to expose that dirt,

36:26.351 --> 36:28.285
       And I am going to make it
              your legacy,

36:28.287 --> 36:29.786
       And then
I’m going to get my client

36:29.788 --> 36:32.923
Once and for all exonerated
for the killing of Hanna dean.

36:34.826 --> 36:37.427
Does that compute, sir?

36:42.601 --> 36:49.472
         [ Slurring ] over my...

36:49.474 --> 36:55.478
                 Dead...body.

36:55.480 --> 36:58.348
Whether you're dead or alive
as this moves forward

36:58.350 --> 37:02.219
Doesn't really concern me.

37:02.221 --> 37:07.924
I would say at this point...
it's not even relevant.

37:10.295 --> 37:15.232
        I hope
your house has termites.

37:20.472 --> 37:22.672
         ¶ My friends ¶
             Jared?

37:22.674 --> 37:24.641
      ¶ They won't listen ¶

37:24.643 --> 37:29.646
       ¶ How it all ends ¶

37:29.648 --> 37:31.982
   ¶ I told them with kisses ¶

37:31.984 --> 37:33.550
                    Hello?

37:33.552 --> 37:34.951
        Hello.

37:34.953 --> 37:37.754
               Who's in there?
who's out there?

37:37.756 --> 37:40.423
  [ Mid-tempo music continues ]

37:40.425 --> 37:42.959
     ¶ And I’ll be your man,
            darling ¶

37:42.961 --> 37:44.828
                What the hell
             are you doing here?

37:44.830 --> 37:47.731
  Would you like me
 to be in your room?

37:47.733 --> 37:49.799
           ¶ I'm gone ¶

37:49.801 --> 37:51.735
You know, this was my room
   for a long time.

37:51.737 --> 37:54.271
    Oh, I remember, all right.
  question is, why are you back?

37:54.273 --> 37:57.307
        ¶ Anybody knows us
         in this place ¶

37:57.309 --> 37:59.643
     Tawney and I
    are separated.

37:59.645 --> 38:01.544
    She's staying
    at the house.

38:02.948 --> 38:04.948
What are <I>you doing here?

38:04.950 --> 38:07.350
       Mom wanted me to check in
               on Jared,

38:07.352 --> 38:09.753
     So I -- I brought some food
         for him and big Ted.

38:09.755 --> 38:13.723
     [ Exhales ]
oh, dad's at Kiwanis.

38:13.725 --> 38:15.525
And Jared's at Claire’s,
     but, hey...

38:15.527 --> 38:18.361
      [ Sighs ]
<I>i'm hungry as a bear.

38:18.363 --> 38:19.896
    ¶ Don't forget your coat ¶

38:19.898 --> 38:21.898
      ¶ It might get cold ¶
  [ sighs ]

38:21.900 --> 38:24.734
  [ Piano music playing ]

38:24.736 --> 38:28.738
                    Well,
              there was no wait.

38:28.740 --> 38:31.708
  But it's not very
  seafoody-looking.

38:31.710 --> 38:35.312
               Of course it is.
             it's got the, um...

38:35.314 --> 38:37.514
                      The...
      thatch?

38:37.516 --> 38:39.916
      ...The thatch
      and the big rope.

38:39.918 --> 38:42.052
       Where's
 the plastic lobster?

38:42.054 --> 38:43.953
      I don't think they do that
           so much any more.

38:43.955 --> 38:46.022
             Waiter:
     good news and bad news.

38:46.024 --> 38:47.490
      We're out of grouper.

38:47.492 --> 38:48.825
You're out of grouper?

38:48.827 --> 38:50.527
     I know -- our speciality.

38:50.529 --> 38:54.531
What's the good news?
     well, we have snapper.

38:54.533 --> 38:57.600
   Snapper?
     it's not that popular.

38:57.602 --> 39:00.937
        Okay.
    snapper it is.

39:00.939 --> 39:02.572
        Excellent choice.

39:04.376 --> 39:05.742
                 We could go
               somewhere else.

39:05.744 --> 39:07.510
          [ Piano music
       continues playing ]

39:07.512 --> 39:09.612
     I'd feel bad
for the piano player.

39:09.614 --> 39:11.948
                 [ Chuckles ]

39:14.753 --> 39:16.553
Thank you for the money,
       mother.

39:16.555 --> 39:20.757
        It's your money, Daniel.
             it always was.

39:20.759 --> 39:23.793
     I just hope
 I can manage things.

39:23.795 --> 39:25.428
               You'll have
         a support system there.

39:25.430 --> 39:27.897
          That's what they do --
               help manage.

39:27.899 --> 39:31.701
      And I’m a phone call away,
               always.

39:31.703 --> 39:33.103
       And, speaking of money...

39:33.105 --> 39:36.706
         Here is your check-book.

39:36.708 --> 39:40.643
            And...your ATM card.

39:40.645 --> 39:44.514
                 Your code is
             Amantha’s birthday.

39:48.019 --> 39:52.021
I don't think anyone here knows
who Amantha is, mother.

39:52.023 --> 39:53.590
                You remember?

39:53.592 --> 39:55.625
        08-11.

39:55.627 --> 39:56.960
                   You do.

39:56.962 --> 40:00.497
          [ Piano music
       continues playing ]

40:06.538 --> 40:09.406
Would you care to dance?

40:09.408 --> 40:12.609
                 [ Chuckles ]
                 I’d love to.

40:21.686 --> 40:25.054
      [ Piano music stops ]

40:27.092 --> 40:29.759
            What does that mean?

40:29.761 --> 40:31.694
    He's on break.
      [ sighs ]

40:33.665 --> 40:36.466
Amantha: I didn't know you liked
      Chinese food, Teddy.

40:36.468 --> 40:38.201
  Got a taste for it
     in college.

40:38.203 --> 40:39.636
         You?

40:39.638 --> 40:41.638
                   Atlanta.

40:41.640 --> 40:43.106
Chopsticks drive me crazy,
       though.

40:43.108 --> 40:44.908
             [ Chuckles softly ]

40:44.910 --> 40:47.177
          I used to practice
      before going out with Jon.

40:47.179 --> 40:48.645
                I didn't want
              to look like a --

40:48.647 --> 40:50.013
    A rube?
                    yeah.

40:50.015 --> 40:52.649
                    Like you.

40:55.587 --> 40:57.854
How are you guys doing,
       anyway?

40:57.856 --> 40:59.656
You and old johnny stern?

40:59.658 --> 41:03.860
              We're not...doing.

41:03.862 --> 41:07.230
Damn, is something in the water
     around here?

41:07.232 --> 41:10.467
                  Something
              in the something.

41:13.839 --> 41:16.840
           Um, you want the rest
            of the mu shu pork?

41:16.842 --> 41:19.242
 Yeah, if you don't.
                 no, go for it.

41:23.014 --> 41:26.583
          I'm really sorry about
          you and Tawney, Teddy.

41:26.585 --> 41:29.219
                 I really hope
                 it works out.

41:29.221 --> 41:30.653
           How it's supposed to.

41:33.625 --> 41:34.924
Maybe it already has.

41:37.028 --> 41:40.096
    Same for you,
     by the way.

41:40.098 --> 41:41.998
           Maybe it already has.

41:46.171 --> 41:47.504
                    What?

41:47.506 --> 41:49.806
     Nothing.
                   say it.

41:49.808 --> 41:51.107
     Nothing.
                 say -- it.

41:51.109 --> 41:53.176
  [ Inhales deeply ]
want to play gin rummy?

41:53.178 --> 41:54.677
                Really, Teddy?

41:54.679 --> 41:56.279
Hey, if you're scared,
    you're scared.

41:56.281 --> 41:57.714
                 [ Laughing ]

41:57.716 --> 41:58.948
      It's fine.

41:58.950 --> 42:00.283
               I haven't played
              in over 10 years,

42:00.285 --> 42:02.852
           And I will still beat
             your red-neck ass.

42:02.854 --> 42:05.288
[ Laughs ] talk is cheap,
  wicked stepsister,

42:05.290 --> 42:07.590
  And old Teddy boy
ain't a teenager any more.

42:07.592 --> 42:09.759
         Okay, Mr. third person.

42:09.761 --> 42:11.928
          You go get the cards,
         and I’ll be right back.

42:11.930 --> 42:14.264
    [ Taps ]
                     [ taps ]

42:14.266 --> 42:16.699
            He bought
       a round-trip ticket?

42:16.701 --> 42:18.067
                     Yep.

42:18.069 --> 42:20.870
           Damn, Carl.
  uh, that don't make any sense.

42:20.872 --> 42:22.772
         I'm telling you,
        he offed himself.

42:24.876 --> 42:27.944
    It's late, Trey. why don't
  we pick this back up tomorrow.

42:27.946 --> 42:29.679
            Unless...

42:29.681 --> 42:32.582
     He was undecided when he
 took the bus up here, you know?

42:32.584 --> 42:34.050
                   Uh-huh.

42:34.052 --> 42:35.552
   You know, and then I didn't
     tell him whatever it was

42:35.554 --> 42:38.588
     That he wanted to hear,
          and he did it.

42:38.590 --> 42:40.223
       Pulled the trigger.

42:40.225 --> 42:42.025
              And you came back
                 a week later

42:42.027 --> 42:43.626
             And tossed his body
                in the river,

42:43.628 --> 42:45.094
      Took his wallet and phone?

42:45.096 --> 42:46.863
    Oh, don't forget the gun.

42:46.865 --> 42:49.599
Then pretended like he was alive
   for the next month or so.

42:49.601 --> 42:51.634
     Look, I panicked, Carl,
              okay?

42:51.636 --> 42:53.903
           I panicked.
    pure dee plain and simple.

42:53.905 --> 42:55.939
        I did some stupid,
         impulsive shit.

42:55.941 --> 42:58.241
     That's his gun, right?
  that's <I>your gun.

42:58.243 --> 42:59.809
  No, the other gun,
  lid -- that one.

42:59.811 --> 43:01.811
That's the one they found
   at his trailer.

43:01.813 --> 43:02.946
              Right,
  that's 'cause I put it there.

43:02.948 --> 43:04.314
      That gun right there,

43:04.316 --> 43:06.349
   That is the gun that I found
        next to his body.

43:06.351 --> 43:09.752
      Why did you put it in
 the trailer -- to frame Holden?

43:09.754 --> 43:13.690
            [ Sighs ]
    to throw you off my trail.

43:14.960 --> 43:17.260
             I know.
          "what trail?"

43:17.262 --> 43:19.862
     I compounded my errors.
           [ chuckles ]

43:19.864 --> 43:21.331
     Look, I -- I wish to god

43:21.333 --> 43:23.866
     That I’d just come clean
   from the get-go, believe me.

43:23.868 --> 43:25.635
               Why don't you
            just come clean now?

43:25.637 --> 43:27.837
   Because there ain't nothing
       to come clean about!

43:27.839 --> 43:29.906
  That's what I’m trying to say!

43:31.042 --> 43:35.645
    [ Sighs ] look, all right,
   there has got to be some way

43:35.647 --> 43:37.146
        That you can prove
       that this is the gun

43:37.148 --> 43:39.148
   That he killed himself with,
              right?

43:39.150 --> 43:42.218
             If we had a bullet,
             state forensics
             might could prove

43:42.220 --> 43:43.886
             That that's the gun
               that killed him.

43:43.888 --> 43:45.655
     Carl, what, do you think
   I took his own gun from him

43:45.657 --> 43:46.956
     And killed him with it?

43:46.958 --> 43:48.191
    I mean, I didn't even know
         he was carrying.

43:49.828 --> 43:52.195
            Okay, Trey,
    we'll go out there tomorrow,

43:52.197 --> 43:53.830
         And you can show me
      where all this took place.

43:53.832 --> 43:56.099
   Bring a damn metal detector,
               too.

43:58.370 --> 44:00.303
                 No problem.

44:02.707 --> 44:04.307
  So, what, do I just meet y'all
       here in the morning?

44:04.309 --> 44:06.142
            Why don't we just
          keep you here tonight,

44:06.144 --> 44:07.410
              And it'll save you
                   a trip?

44:07.412 --> 44:11.280
                      ¶¶

44:13.118 --> 44:15.652
        You never even had
         any kettle corn.

44:30.001 --> 44:32.702
    Oh, I declare.

44:32.704 --> 44:34.837
                 Hey, buddy.

44:34.839 --> 44:36.005
          Who's winning?

44:36.007 --> 44:37.106
                  Don't ask.

44:40.712 --> 44:41.944
        Where has he been?

44:41.946 --> 44:44.147
         Well, your dad gave him
                to Daniel.

44:44.149 --> 44:45.682
          Daniel gave him to me.

44:45.684 --> 44:47.784
              And I’m giving him
              back to the store.

44:47.786 --> 44:49.986
              Where he belongs.

44:52.257 --> 44:54.791
    I kind of miss
  the little fella.

44:54.793 --> 44:56.059
              Shut up and draw.

44:59.397 --> 45:03.332
     I'll deny I ever said this,
              but, uh...

45:03.334 --> 45:04.767
              The kitchen looks
                 pretty good.

45:08.139 --> 45:09.172
           Can I play?

45:09.174 --> 45:11.774
                      No.
       no.

45:18.483 --> 45:22.452
                      ¶¶

45:27.492 --> 45:29.025
                  [ Sighs ]

45:32.397 --> 45:33.963
         I swear to god.

45:33.965 --> 45:36.866
              For the 10th time.

45:39.738 --> 45:41.404
   Just have them keep looking,
              Carl.

45:41.406 --> 45:45.875
He can't get down there, Trey.
the river's too high.

45:45.877 --> 45:47.810
         I'm telling you,

45:47.812 --> 45:52.448
  That is where George was at --
   right there -- and his gun.

45:54.486 --> 45:57.754
We'll just have to wait till the
river goes down to come back.

45:57.756 --> 46:00.323
    Oh, that'll take a while.

46:00.325 --> 46:03.793
Like finding a needle
in a haystack anyhow.

46:03.795 --> 46:05.795
      [ Sighs ]

46:05.797 --> 46:09.465
                      ¶¶

46:10.401 --> 46:13.803
Trey Willis, you're under arrest
for the murder of George Melton.

46:13.805 --> 46:15.538
Sheriff Daggett: you have
the right to remain silent.

46:15.540 --> 46:18.040
          Jesus, Carl!
anything you say can and will
be held against you...

46:18.042 --> 46:20.076
         Can't do this!
...in a court of law.

46:20.078 --> 46:21.344
      I didn't kill George!

46:21.346 --> 46:22.812
   You have a right
to speak to an attorney

46:22.814 --> 46:24.914
 And have him present
 during questioning.

46:42.567 --> 46:44.167
        [ Brake engages ]

46:44.169 --> 46:45.868
       [ Engine shuts off ]

46:45.870 --> 46:48.871
                  [ Sighs ]

46:53.378 --> 46:57.280
   Brave new world.
      [ sighs ]

46:57.282 --> 46:58.881
            It's only temporary,
                   honey.

46:58.883 --> 47:01.951
I've never had a roommate
       before.

47:04.122 --> 47:05.388
           I thought about that.

47:05.390 --> 47:08.891
   Get to practice
my interpersonal skills.

47:08.893 --> 47:11.394
       It's a lifelong practice.
          I’ll tell you that.

47:11.396 --> 47:12.995
 [ Chuckles softly ]

47:16.401 --> 47:18.467
                   1, 2, 3.

47:18.469 --> 47:20.403
       [ Metal screeching ]

47:20.405 --> 47:21.971
                  [ Sighs ]

47:21.973 --> 47:25.007
         [ Both exhale ]

47:26.144 --> 47:28.878
 Fits like a glove.
                    it does.

47:33.618 --> 47:35.184
Don't look bad, does it?

47:35.186 --> 47:36.886
               No, it doesn't.

47:42.126 --> 47:43.626
    Gonna need you
a new refrigerator now.

47:43.628 --> 47:46.028
                 [ Chuckles ]

47:50.368 --> 47:52.602
        I need to say something,
                  son.

47:52.604 --> 47:56.606
I don't want to talk about this,
         dad.

48:02.080 --> 48:06.015
               When Margaret --
             your mother left...

48:06.017 --> 48:09.252
     I didn't say a lot about it
        because I felt guilty.

48:09.254 --> 48:12.154
                    I felt
              like I failed you.

48:12.156 --> 48:16.492
Well, I felt like it was
my fault somehow -- her leaving.

48:16.494 --> 48:18.561
               I see that now.

48:18.563 --> 48:21.597
I mean, the whole time
 I’ve been married...

48:21.599 --> 48:24.066
I've been afraid Tawney was
gonna do the same thing, dad.

48:26.004 --> 48:28.471
       She did.

48:28.473 --> 48:32.341
                      ¶¶

48:35.413 --> 48:38.648
      I should've told you this,
                but...

48:38.650 --> 48:41.150
                 It wasn't
           all Margaret’s fault.

48:42.587 --> 48:45.254
                  I mean,
           she had her problems.

48:45.256 --> 48:48.457
        And we got more and more
            distant, but...

48:48.459 --> 48:50.359
    But what, dad?

48:50.361 --> 48:54.697
              I started leaning
              on somebody else.

48:54.699 --> 48:56.065
                Another woman.

48:57.368 --> 49:00.703
         Wasn't physical,
 just -- just talking and stuff,

49:00.705 --> 49:03.673
              But as soon
        as I opened that door...

49:05.543 --> 49:09.445
   ...I sure didn't do what I
could have to save the marriage.

49:09.447 --> 49:13.482
              I just let her go.

49:13.484 --> 49:17.353
                      ¶¶

49:26.397 --> 49:29.065
  I just hope you do all you can
          to save yours.

49:47.618 --> 49:51.253
                   Well...

49:54.058 --> 49:57.426
  Don't take this the wrong way,
          mother, but...

49:57.428 --> 49:59.462
                I'd like to do
               this part alone.

49:59.464 --> 50:03.466
      Oh. okay.

50:03.468 --> 50:06.235
              I'm gonna give it
                my best shot.

50:06.237 --> 50:07.703
   I know you will.

50:07.705 --> 50:09.605
            All I can do, right?

50:09.607 --> 50:12.008
It's all anybody can do.

50:20.284 --> 50:21.650
          Can you do me a favour?

50:21.652 --> 50:24.587
      Of course.

50:24.589 --> 50:28.791
               Would you try
           and forgive yourself?

50:28.793 --> 50:33.362
               You did the best
                 you could...

50:36.200 --> 50:38.801
      ...Out of the most unusual
          of circumstances.

50:38.803 --> 50:42.605
                      ¶¶

50:42.607 --> 50:44.707
I'll give it my best shot.

50:53.618 --> 50:56.552
      [ Sighs ]
all we can do, right?

50:56.554 --> 50:58.721
 [ Sighs, sniffles ]

51:02.360 --> 51:05.394
                  See you
            in the funny papers.

51:05.396 --> 51:09.198
                      ¶¶

51:56.547 --> 51:58.514
            [ Sighs ]

